    "value": "The RADARSAT program is a fleet of three generations of Canadian Earth observation satellites using synthetic aperture radar (SAR) technology: RADARSAT-1, RADARSAT-2, and the RADARSAT Constellation Mission (RCM). RADARSAT-1 was Canada's first operational Earth observation satellite; RADARSAT-2 is operated commercially by MDA; the RCM consists of three identical satellites, and RCM data is used in maritime surveillance, ecosystem monitoring, and disaster relief efforts.",
